DTSTART:20260330T170000Z
DTEND:20260330T180000Z
LOCATION:GLOBAL &amp\; INTERNATIONAL STUDIES BUILDING - Room Number: GA1060
GEO:39.170002;-86.517492
SUMMARY:We Aren't Supposed to Be Here: A Humanities Workshop on Belonging
DESCRIPTION:This workshop creates space to reflect on what it means to en
 ter and navigate academia as a first-generation student\, especially when
  graduate study was never imagined as a possible path\, and so many of th
 e rules and expectations must be learned without a map.  Drawing on a jou
 rney from film translation to liberal arts and R1 institutions\, alongsid
 e experience in faculty and administrative leadership\, it considers how 
 academic trajectories are shaped not simply by merit and resilience\, but
  by access to mentoring\, sponsorship\, and institutional support.  How c
 an we make academia more supportive and inclusive so that no one has to f
 ind their way alone?
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  This workshop creates space to reflect 
 on what it means to enter and navigate academia as a first-generation stu
 dent\, especially when graduate study was never imagined as a possible pa
 th\, and so many of the rules and expectations must be learned without a 
 map.<br />  Drawing on a journey from film translation to liberal arts an
 d R1 institutions\, alongside experience in faculty and administrative le
 adership\, it considers how academic trajectories are shaped not simply b
 y merit and resilience\, but by access to mentoring\, sponsorship\, and i
 nstitutional support.<br />  How can we make academia more supportive and
  inclusive so that no one has to find their way alone?</p>
UID:20260330T170000Z-2235361@events.iu.edu
