 University Bloomington. He holds a Master's degree in Water Resources Eng
 ineering and is passionate about the intersection of environmental policy
 \, socio-environmental systems\, and complex systems modeling. His resear
 ch focuses on the dynamic interplay between human decision-making and env
 ironmental processes\, using agent-based modeling to investigate complex 
 interactions within socio-environmental systems.</p><p><strong>About the 
